article.headline: Old Dominion 85, Northeastern 79
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Isaiah Hunter scored 19 of his 21 points in the second half as Old Dominion rallied from a 13-point halftime deficit to defeat Northeastern 85-79 Saturday. The Monarchs (10-4, 4-1 Colonial Athletic Association) trailed 42-29 after shooting only 31 percent from the field in the first half. But Brian Henderson hit a 3-pointer and a layup during an 11-2 run that cut the Huskies' lead to 51-50, and Hunter scored on a fast-break layup to put Old Dominion ahead 64-63 with just over 10 minutes left. Henderson hit his fourth 3 of the game to stretch the lead to four, and Northeastern (7-6, 3-2) could get no closer. Jose Juan Barea scored 32 points and handed out 10 assists for the Huskies. Bennet Davis added 13 points, and Shawn James and Bobby Kelly scored 12 apiece. Henderson, Valdas Vasylius and Arnaud Dahi each scored 16 points for the Monarchs, who shot 55 percent from the field in the second half. Dahi also had 10 rebounds.
